import numpy as np

def algorithm(train_samples, train_parity, test_samples):
    n = train_samples.shape[1]
    aug_matrix = np.hstack((train_samples, train_parity.reshape(-1, 1)))
    print("Augmented Matrix: ", aug_matrix)  # <== print statement

    # Reorder the matrix rows in descending order of leading zeros
    leading_zeros = np.apply_along_axis(lambda x: len(x) - np.argmax(x), 1, aug_matrix)
    print("Leading Zeros: ", leading_zeros)  # <== print statement
    aug_matrix = aug_matrix[np.argsort(-leading_zeros)]
    print("Re-ordered Matrix: ", aug_matrix)  # <== print statement

    for i in range(n):
        pivot = np.argmax(aug_matrix[i:, i])
        pivot_row = pivot + i
        print(f"Pivot: {pivot}, Pivot Row: {pivot_row}")  # <== print statement
        if aug_matrix[pivot_row, i] == 0:
            continue  # Skip this iteration if the pivot column is zero
        for j in range(i + 1, len(aug_matrix)):
            if aug_matrix[j, i] == 1:
                aug_matrix[j] = (aug_matrix[j] - aug_matrix[i]) % 2
        print(f"Augmented Matrix after {i+1} iteration: ", aug_matrix)  # <== print statement
                
    true_bits = np.zeros(n, dtype=int)
    for i in reversed(range(n)):
        true_bits[i] = aug_matrix[i, n]
        for j in range(i + 1, n):
            if aug_matrix[i, j] == 1:
                true_bits[i] ^= true_bits[j]
        print(f"True Bits after {n-i} iteration: ", true_bits)  # <== print statement
                
    test_parity = np.dot(test_samples, true_bits) % 2
    print("Test Parity: ", test_parity)  # <== print statement
    return test_parity
